name: Tennessee tornado
summary: Severe weather, including tornadoes, has left a trail of destruction across Tennessee and North Carolina, causing three fatalities and leaving a 900-mile path of damage. The Nashville area was particularly hard-hit, with an EF-3 tornado causing significant damage in Columbia. The Southeast has been lashed by additional severe weather, including tornadoes, following the deadly storms earlier in Tennessee. Two tornadoes were reported in Middle Tennessee, while three tornadoes have been confirmed in Michigan, resulting in one fatality. Storm-tracking resources, such as tornado watches and warnings, are crucial for emergency preparedness during these events. Despite the devastation, the Nashville community is finding hope and resilience amid the aftermath of the tornadoes, while weather service crews are assessing the extent of the damage in Columbia, Tennessee.

name: Jimmy Johnson
summary: Jimmy Johnson, a legendary American football player, has passed away at the age of 86. Known for his exceptional defensive skills, Johnson played 16 seasons for the San Francisco 49ers, earning a place in the Pro Football Hall of Fame. He was a key member of the 49ers' 1957 NFL championship team and also played for the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA), where he was an All-American. Johnson's passing has been met with tributes from former teammates, coaches, and fans, who remember him as a talented athlete and a true icon of the sport.

name: Steve Albini
summary: Steve Albini, the renowned producer, musician, and frontman of Big Black and Shellac, has passed away at the age of 61. Albini left an indelible mark on rock music, collaborating with iconic bands like Nirvana and the Pixies. His innovative production techniques, characterized by minimalism and raw intensity, shaped the sound of countless albums. Albini's legacy as an influential figure extends beyond his production work, as he was a vocal advocate for independent music and a tireless supporter of emerging artists. His passing is a profound loss for the music industry, and he will be remembered as a creative visionary who forever changed the landscape of rock music.
